Sentencas: RBa(Co,M)(4)O7 (R = Y, Ca, In and M = Zn, Fe, Al) oxides with a hexagonal structure and corner-shared (Co,M)O-4 tetrahedra have been synthesized and investigated as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC).
Titulo: Low Thermal Expansion RBa(Co,M)4O7 Cathode Materials Based on Tetrahedral-Site Cobalt Ions for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Among the various compositions investigated, YBaCo4-xZnxO7 (1 <= x <= 2) shows long-term stability at high temperatures.
Titulo: Low Thermal Expansion RBa(Co,M)4O7 Cathode Materials Based on Tetrahedral-Site Cobalt Ions for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) values of the RBa(Co, M)(4)O-7 specimens were determined to be 6 x 10(-6) to 13 x 10(-6)
Titulo: Low Thermal Expansion RBa(Co,M)4O7 Cathode Materials Based on Tetrahedral-Site Cobalt Ions for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: degrees C-1 in the range of 80-900 degrees C, which provides good thermal expansion compatibility with the standard SOFC electrolyte materials.
Titulo: Low Thermal Expansion RBa(Co,M)4O7 Cathode Materials Based on Tetrahedral-Site Cobalt Ions for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The low TEC is attributed to the absence of spin state transitions of tetrahedral-site Co2+/3+ ions and relatively small amount of oxygen loss with increasing temperature.
Titulo: Low Thermal Expansion RBa(Co,M)4O7 Cathode Materials Based on Tetrahedral-Site Cobalt Ions for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The YBaCo3ZnO7 + GDC composite cathodes exhibit low polarization resistance and good fuel cell performance comparable to that of well-studied Co-based perovskite cathodes, but With the critical advantage of ail ideal matching of the TEC value with those of standard electrolytes.
Titulo: Low Thermal Expansion RBa(Co,M)4O7 Cathode Materials Based on Tetrahedral-Site Cobalt Ions for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
